                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#2v">Fol. 2v</locus>: Note concerning events in the lives (?) of Evangelists (Matthew, Mark, Luke and John).<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Hardly readable.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#98rb">Fols. 98rb-99</locus>ra: Text concerning the value of common orthodox prayers.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           In Amharic.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#99ra">Fol. 99ra</locus>: Note concerning dates of celebrating some feasts, with a small, crude calendaric table.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in Gǝʿǝz and Amharic.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#99va">Fol. 99va</locus>: Unidentified text.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           In Amharic. Recent and hardly readable, written in pink.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#99vb">Fol. 99vb</locus>: ʾAsmat-prayer. <q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The title (?)  is written in the upper margin: “And you who have terrified the idols...”.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6">
                           <locus target="#100v">Fol. 100v</locus>: Protective prayer to God, a recipe for a certain medicine, and a short protective prayer mentioning St. Mary.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written in Gǝʿǝz and Amharic.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- A chain of black dots and a red line, probably separating the text passages (?), on fols.: 21v, 23r, 41r, 41v, 42v, 49r, 50r, 53r, 61v, 62v, 63r, 64v, 67r, 71r, 72r, 73r, 77v, 87r, 93v.&#xD;
- Crude drawing of a cross with an inscription above: zǝ-Mäsqäl zä-ʾAbba, fol. 1r.&#xD;
- Numerous corrections of the text (written interlineally and in the margins) by another hand: fols. 3va, 4rab, 4vab, 5rab, 6rab, 9va, 10rab, 10vb, 51va, 73vb, 84vb. &#xD;
- Text erasures: fol. 29rab. &#xD;
- Crudely written notes in pen: fols. 6r, 17v, 75v, 100rv.</item>
